<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-27T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-27T09:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10937: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-27T22:00:00+08:00">June 27, 1930—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 29—12:30 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>510. 1. Canton’s June 24, 1 p.m.<note n="48" xml:id="d127fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> has been repeated to the American Consuls at
                            Foochow, Amoy and Swatow.</p>
                        <p>2. Following from American Consul at Foochow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“June 27, 10 a.m. Your June 26, 1 p.m.<note n="48" xml:id="d127fn2">Not printed.</note> Ironsides apparently
                                    coming to join Lu Hsing-pang. Lu recently appointed Commander
                                        <pb facs="0236" n="138" xml:id="pg_138"/> of Eighth Army and
                                    Governor of Fukien by the Northern Coalition. Thirty-six
                                    Americans still in Lu territory unable to evacuate. River
                                    completely blocked.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Commander in Chief.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>